thread.title: State colleges: Utah women's soccer coach gets 150th career win
thread.title_full: State colleges: Utah women's soccer coach gets 150th career win | The Salt Lake Tribune

title: State colleges: Utah women's soccer coach gets 150th career win
text:
Corvallis, Ore. • Mariah Elmer scored in the 39th minute and Lindsey Luke picked up her third shutout of the season as the Utah women's soccer team defeated Oregon State, 1-0, Friday to give coach Rich Manning his 150th career win.
Elmer's goal, her third of the season, gave the Utes (4-4-3, 1-1-0 Pac-12) their third consecutive victory over the Beavers (4-3-3, 0-2-0).
Weber State 3, North Dakota 2 • With the clock winding down in overtime, junior defender Kellyn Ashby scored after a scramble following a corner kick, lifting Weber State over North Dakota at Grand Forks, N.D.
  Weber State (5-6-1 overall, 1-2-0 Big Sky) took a season-high 32 shots to just 12 for North Dakota (3-6-1, 1-1-0) and had an 18-5 advantage on shots on goal. 
Montana 2, Southern Utah 1 • At Missoula, Mont., Abbie Flandro broke a scoreless tie in the 79th minute, but the Grizzlies got the equalizer in the 86th minute and added the game-winner about a minute later. The Thunderbirds fell to 5-6 overall, 0-3 in the Big Sky Conference. Montana improved to 4-7-1, 1-2-0.
Westminster 2, MSU Denver 0 • Friday's game at Salt Lake City was delayed more than an hour by lightning and hail, but once the Griffins (6-3, 3-3 RMAC) were able to take the pitch, they blanked the Roadrunners (4-3-2, 1-2-2) for their second shutout in a row. Korral Koehler had two assists, setting up headers by Rylei North and Madison Roemer.

Men's soccer
Fort Lewis College 3, Westminster 0 • At Durango, Colo., the Griffins (1-6, 0-5 RMAC) lost their fifth consecutive game while the Skyhawks (7-2, 4-0) remained perfect in RMAC play.

Women's volleyball
Western New Mexico 3, Westminster 0 • At Silver City, N.M., the Griffins (4-10, 1-5 RMAC) recorded only 23 kills in losing to the Mustangs (11-3, 6-0).

Men's cross country
At South Bend, Indiana, Southern Utah placed fourth at the Joe Paine Notre Dame Cross Country Invitational. Hayden Hawks led the Thunderbirds, ranked No. 23 in the nation, by taking fifth in the 5-mile race with a time of 23 minutes, 55.4 seconds.

Women's cross country
Sarah Feeny (seventh)and Hannah McInturff (ninth) led Utah to a fifth-place finish at the Joe Paine Notre Dame Cross Country Invitational.
